The paper is about visual question answering (VQA), which is a task that involves both computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different types of visual features and proposes a new approach, which involves using grid features instead of region-based features. This makes the paper relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on different datasets and tasks, including image captioning, which makes it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
